						               													<description>A family card game which leads to story creation, supporting logical thinking and improving perceptual abilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You play saviors of the mysterious realm Magicon, which suffers the invasions of the dark forces. Your party travels to the outskirts of Magicon, but only one of you will succeed. Which one of you is the chosen one who will make the journey to the Wizardon? Who is the one who becomes the savior of the eternal light, entrusts them to the hands of the Great Mage and ignites the hope for the whole Magicon?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A strategy game for 2-6 players. The goal of each round of the game is to get rid of all the cards. You place your cards one by one so that the color markings expressing the journey through the land of Magicon. The score depends on the last card dealt. The more northern the region, the more points. It doesn't matter whether the player finished sooner or later.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is played on multiple rounds. Every time the game is finished, players mark their points on the scoring board with a playing figure of the chosen color. Whoever reach 10 points on the scoring boar, wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
